oc:kn_0a23d931 a oc:KnowledgeNode,
        oc:OutputFormat ;
    oc:appliesToContext "When generating the final crypto report document" ;
    oc:directiveContent """# Crypto Research Report: {TokenName} ({TICKER})
**Network**: {Blockchain} | **Category**: {Category} | **Date**: {Date}
## Executive Summary → Rating + Risk Level
## Key Metrics Table (Price, MC, FDV, Supply, TVL, Volume, Rank)
## 1. Project Overview (What, Problem/Solution, Tech, Team, Roadmap)
## 2. Tokenomics (Utility, Supply Dynamics, Distribution, Vesting, Value Accrual)
## 3. On-Chain Analysis (Activity, Holders, Network Health)
## 4. Market Analysis (Competitive Landscape, Position, Adoption)
## 5. Valuation (Relative Metrics, Bull/Bear Cases)
## 6. Risk Analysis (Key Risks Table, Red Flags Checklist)
## 7. Investment Thesis (Bull/Bear/Catalysts)
## Conclusion (Rating + Conviction + Watchpoints)
## Disclaimer + Sources""" ;
    oc:templateVariables "Blockchain",
        "Category",
        "Date",
        "TICKER",
        "TokenName" .

oc:kn_154c0d00 a oc:AntiPattern,
        oc:KnowledgeNode ;
    oc:appliesToContext "When generating any crypto report output" ;
    oc:directiveContent "Never present analysis as investment advice or price predictions. Always include the standard disclaimer that the report is for informational purposes only." ;
    oc:hasRationale "Crypto investments are highly speculative; presenting analysis as advice creates legal and ethical liability" ;
    oc:severityLevel "CRITICAL" .

oc:kn_45777464 a oc:AssumptionBoundary,
        oc:KnowledgeNode ;
    oc:appliesToContext "When user provides minimal data" ;
    oc:directiveContent "Analysis quality is directly proportional to the amount of on-chain data and context the user provides. Without user-supplied metrics, the report will be more qualitative and less quantitative." ;
    oc:hasRationale "The skill cannot fetch live data; garbage in = garbage out for metric-heavy sections" ;
    oc:severityLevel "MEDIUM" .

oc:kn_48eaf5de a oc:Constraint,
        oc:KnowledgeNode ;
    oc:appliesToContext "Always — before beginning any crypto analysis" ;
    oc:directiveContent "Cannot access real-time prices, on-chain data, or audit smart contracts. Analysis is limited to publicly available information provided by the user." ;
    oc:hasRationale "The skill has no live data feeds; all metrics must be user-supplied or derived from public knowledge" ;
    oc:severityLevel "HIGH" .

oc:kn_5cb3e8bc a oc:KnowledgeNode,
        oc:Procedure ;
    oc:appliesToContext "When generating a crypto research report" ;
    oc:directiveContent "1. Gather project basics (name, ticker, network, category, available metrics) 2. Select analysis scope (Quick Overview, Deep Dive, Tokenomics Focus, or Technical Review) 3. Apply category-specific metrics framework 4. Analyze tokenomics (supply, distribution, vesting, value accrual) 5. Assess on-chain metrics and network health 6. Position competitively and value relatively 7. Generate bull/bear thesis with risk assessment 8. Produce formatted report with disclaimer" ;
    oc:stepOrder 1 .

oc:kn_6e78a907 a oc:Heuristic,
        oc:KnowledgeNode ;
    oc:appliesToContext "When analyzing token distribution tables" ;
    oc:directiveContent "Flag team allocation >25% and investor allocation >30% as concerning. Community allocation >40% is generally positive. These thresholds serve as quick distribution health checks." ;
    oc:hasRationale "Excessive insider allocation signals misaligned incentives and potential dump risk; community-heavy distribution suggests healthier decentralization" ;
    oc:severityLevel "MEDIUM" .

oc:kn_751f4d35 a oc:Heuristic,
        oc:KnowledgeNode ;
    oc:appliesToContext "When scoping the analysis framework for a project" ;
    oc:directiveContent "Use category-specific key metrics as the primary analysis lens: L1→TPS/TVL/Dev Activity, L2→TVL/TXns/Fee Savings, DeFi→TVL/Volume/Revenue, Stablecoins→MarketCap/Peg Stability." ;
    oc:hasRationale "Different project categories have fundamentally different value drivers; applying generic metrics leads to superficial analysis" ;
    oc:severityLevel "MEDIUM" .

oc:kn_84842e7a a oc:CodePattern,
        oc:KnowledgeNode ;
    oc:appliesToContext "When performing relative valuation of a crypto token" ;
    oc:directiveContent """## Valuation Metrics
- Market Cap / TVL
- FDV / Revenue (annualized)
- P/S Ratio (Protocol Revenue)
- MC / Active Users
- Token Value Accrual: fee distribution, buyback/burn, staking rewards, governance rights""" .

oc:kn_cc7de754 a oc:DesignPrinciple,
        oc:KnowledgeNode ;
    oc:appliesToContext "When composing the investment thesis and conclusion sections" ;
    oc:directiveContent "Structure every report with balanced bull/bear cases, explicit risk factors with likelihood/impact ratings, and a clear conviction level to avoid directional bias." ;
    oc:hasRationale "Balanced analysis prevents confirmation bias and gives readers a complete picture for their own decision-making" ;
    oc:severityLevel "HIGH" .

oc:kn_d87ae9e7 a oc:KnowledgeNode,
        oc:SecurityImplication ;
    oc:appliesToContext "When performing risk analysis" ;
    oc:directiveContent "Always check for red flags: anonymous team, unaudited contracts, high team allocation, no real utility, concentrated holdings. Present these as a checklist." ;
    oc:hasRationale "These are the most common indicators of risky or fraudulent crypto projects; missing them exposes users to scams" ;
    oc:severityLevel "CRITICAL" .

